# API Memory
# Loaded when: api, routes, endpoints, tRPC, REST, validation mentioned

@meta: keywords=api,routes,endpoints,trpc,rest,validation | priority=high | updated=2026-03-05

## STRUCTURE
base: src/api
routes: src/api/routes/*.ts | auto-loaded by src/api/index.ts
middleware: src/api/middleware/*.ts
schemas: src/api/schemas/*.ts | Zod validation

## TECH
rest: Express 4.x | JSON responses
trpc: @trpc/server@10.x | type-safe RPC
validation: Zod | all inputs validated
serialization: superjson | handles Date, Map, Set

## REST ROUTES
prefix: /api/v1

# User routes
GET /users | query:{page,limit,search} | returns:User[]
GET /users/:id | returns:User
PATCH /users/:id | body:Partial<User> | returns:User
DELETE /users/:id | soft delete | returns:{success}

# Posts routes
GET /posts | query:{page,limit,userId} | returns:Post[]
POST /posts | body:{title,content} | auth:required | returns:Post
GET /posts/:id | returns:Post
PATCH /posts/:id | body:Partial<Post> | auth:owner | returns:Post
DELETE /posts/:id | auth:owner | returns:{success}

## tRPC ROUTER
location: src/api/trpc/router.ts
endpoint: /trpc

routers:
  user: queries[getById,getAll] | mutations[update,delete]
  post: queries[getById,getAll,getByUser] | mutations[create,update,delete]
  auth: mutations[register,login,logout,refresh]

context: {user?,req,res} | user added by auth middleware

## MIDDLEWARE CHAIN
1. helmet | security headers
2. cors | allow:localhost:3000,app.domain.com
3. rate-limit | 100req/15min per IP
4. body-parser | json + urlencoded
5. auth (optional) | validates JWT if present
6. route handler
7. error-handler | catches all errors

## VALIDATION
input: Zod schemas | src/api/schemas/*.ts
pattern: validate at handler entry | fail fast with 400
errors: ZodError → formatted {field,message}[]

example:
```typescript
const CreatePostSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1).max(200),
  content: z.string().min(1),
  tags: z.array(z.string()).optional()
})
```

## RESPONSE FORMAT
success: {data:T} | status:200
created: {data:T} | status:201
error: {error:{message,code,details?}} | status:4xx/5xx

pagination: {data:T[], meta:{page,limit,total,hasMore}}

## ERROR HANDLING
errors inherit from: AppError | src/errors/AppError.ts
types: ValidationError(400) | UnauthorizedError(401) | ForbiddenError(403) | NotFoundError(404) | ConflictError(409)
middleware: src/api/middleware/errorHandler.ts | catches all | logs | responds

## CONVENTIONS
- Use plural nouns: /users not /user
- Use HTTP verbs properly: GET(read) POST(create) PATCH(update) DELETE(delete)
- Nest resources: /users/:id/posts not /posts?userId=:id
- Version in URL: /v1/users
- Always validate input
- Always return typed responses
- Never expose internal errors

## PERF
- Response compression: gzip
- Caching headers: Cache-Control, ETag
- DB query optimization: use select, include wisely
- Pagination: default limit:20 | max:100
